task.summary:
Bugfixes on chip.load_devices Added functionality to do 'for dev on chip' instead of 'for dev on chip.devices'
Added chip template files for thermo01 and thermo02
Experiment will reload, no need to restart qtlab.

Added features: - signal switcher (arduino based), automatic switching based on script filename, or override using script function - multiple experiments per device, plus the ability to completely stop the automation, skip the remaining experiments of the current device or even run additional experiments on the current, or even another device before continuing normal program flow - new driver for the HP (work in progress, currently only has a constant output voltage, or a triangle sweep), if you require more, use the standard qt instrument. - script automatically skips devices that have no experiments configured - added the function chip.limit_range which comes in handy when doing experiments on chip quarters - QT Data storing and plotting has been wrapped in the data.py import. Simply create a data object: data = data(name='%s_IV' % name, dev = dev, coordinates='Vsd', values='Isd') for example. Add data using data.fill(v,i), plot it using data.plot() and close the data using data.close(). - new eburn function is still work in progress

bugfixes and features: - data object now has a changeable basepath. It'll be automatically set to c:/dataYYYY/FOLDER, where YYYY is the current year, and FOLDER is the same foldername as where your 'main.py' script is in. - probably more, but didnt keep track, sorry :)
experiments can (and probably should) be put in the 'experiments' folder from now on.
templates should from now on be located in the templates folder.
